comments: Washington (CHA) places his hand on George's (LAC) side and marginal contact occurs as they move in the same direction.
Jackson (LAC) delivers contact as he sets the pick on Rozier (CHA).
Morris Sr. (LAC) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent before the shot is imminent.
George (LAC) legally contests Rozier's (CHA) jump shot attempt.
Leonard (LAC) engages with McDaniels (CHA) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Leonard releases away to retrieve the post entry pass.
McDaniels (CHA) absorbs the contact from Leonard (LAC) in the post and marginal body contact occurs as he defends Leonard in the post.
Morris Sr. (LAC) and Washington (CHA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
George (LAC) brings his hand towards Rozier's (CHA) side and marginal contact occurs as Rozier receives the pass.
Washington (CHA) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Plumlee (CHA) and Morris Sr. (LAC) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Morris Sr. (LAC) establishes himself in Washington's (CHA) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Jackson (LAC) establishes himself in Oubre Jr.'s (CHA) path and is firming up as he absorbs the contact.
Oubre Jr. (CHA) places a resting hand to Leonard's (LAC) back and marginal body contact occurs as Leonard receives the ball.
Morris Sr. (LAC) establishes himself in McDaniels's (CHA) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
George (LAC) cleanly dislodges the ball from McDaniels (CHA), and the ensuing body contact is marginal.

Oubre Jr. (CHA) contests Leonard's (LAC) shot near the rim and some contact occurs to Leonard's head.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Washington (CHA) establishes himself in George's (LAC) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Leonard (LAC) brings his arm toward Rozier's (CHA) path and marginal contact occurs during Rozier's drive.
Jackson (LAC) and Plumlee (CHA) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Leonard (LAC) does not overtly or abruptly extend his leg out as incidental contact occurs with McDaniels (CHA) during the jump shot attempt.
Mann (LAC) and Washington (CHA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
The Hornets are awarded a timeout prior to a potential five second violation.
Leonard (LAC) and McDaniels (CHA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
George (LAC) steps slightly forward towards Rozier (CHA) and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Rozier (CHA) establishes himself in Batum's (LAC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
McDaniels (CHA) establishes himself in George's (LAC) path and absorbs the contact.
Batum (LAC) briefly grasps Washington's (CHA) arm and quickly disengages as he gathers the inbound entry.
Batum (LAC) legally contests Washington's (CHA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
